<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid fees cut in half</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I think that's the key... smaller raid requires more buffs to succeed, and what I have extra right now will cover a few small raids of extra buffs.  With 9 groups last night, we went through a total of 1 stack of peridots.  That's not going to happen often, we happened to have the right support to do it, but it does help out the treasury a tiny bit for future rune/coffin needs.<br>
<br>
A larger raid is also more likely to succeed and not need coffins, barring a couple in the pits occasionally in Perma.  Even then, with the right classes available, you don't necessarily need coffins to recover the corpses.<br>
<br>
Looking at the current trend, I think we're going to start seeing bigger dragon raids overall, due to more guilds dropping out of these particular rotations.  With that in mind, I think the ~3.5pp extra per raider should cover the few coffins we are likely to need, the few times we need them.  If we do have a major wipe-out, we'll deal with it then. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
