Coffins are very expensive, like 160pp each.  While the raid fee does cover that, it is only a last resort.  I think Korban took a loss that raid.  I know he does not mind paying for it and probably blamed himself for the failure, but a KCoG leader is a volunteer not a piggy bank.<br>
<br>
I am of the opinion that you should keep the 30pp until you have a large buffer, say 20 or 30 coffins worth (3-4k).  Paying 30pp does not hurt the pocket book.  For the raid leader to collect for coffins after a failure when people want to leave can be a pain.<br>
If you can't trust your raid leaders with the cash, how can you trust them to lead you into battle?<br>
<br>
Just my opinion,<br>
Lonium/Tonson<br>
<br>
PS I also remember the last Fear failure.  CR was caused by someone who didn't listen and sat pulling a train.  CR took 2 hours longer than it should because people would not listen and would train.<br>
Yes, I have issues with listening.  I have great patients for questions though.<br>
